WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.272
[Python Functions Mastery] Welcome to Python Functions Mastery. Today, we'll learn how to write reusable and modular code.

00:00:07.272 --> 00:00:16.631
[Defining a Function] A function is defined using the 'def' keyword, followed by the function name and parentheses. Indentation is key for the scope.

00:00:16.631 --> 00:00:24.671
[Code Comparison] Functions can be simple or advanced. Advanced functions use parameters and return values to be more flexible.

00:00:24.671 --> 00:00:32.064
[Flow of Data] Data flows into functions via arguments, gets processed, and is sent back via return statements.

00:00:32.064 --> 00:00:40.079
[Key Metrics] Functions provide 100% reusability and make code maintenance significantly easier as your app grows.

00:00:40.079 --> 00:00:47.327
[Conclusion] In summary, following the DRY principle with functions makes your Python code clean and professional.
